name: ecommerce_micro
description: Microservices-based system that manages a simple e-commerce application. The system should handle user authentication, product management, and order processing. Emphasis will be placed on implementing concurrency control and ensuring the system can handle clustering for high availability.

description: Our notification microservice leverages Kafka to efficiently manage and distribute notifications. This microservice consumes messages from Kafka topics, enabling seamless delivery of notifications to users in real-time. By utilizing Kafka's scalable and reliable messaging system.

name: Booking-Service
description: Booking Microservice. Part of Airline Backend Management System. Along with handling the booking logic, it also acts as a producer for the message queue which is consumed by the Reminder Service to send email
